{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9ebce55-761c-4675-9901-d89ff1d71038","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code, here's exactly what you need:\n\n### Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<!-- SettingsPage.xaml -->\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element. This tells the XAML compiler to resolve all `{Binding …}` expressions against `SettingsViewModel` at **compile time**.\n\n### Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit build errors for typos (e.g. `{Binding Themee}` → **XC0045**). To make this even stricter, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding warnings as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| **XC0045** | Property not found on the `x:DataType` type |\n| **XC0022** | Type mismatch in binding expression |\n\n### Rules to remember\n\n1. **Every `{Binding}` in scope of `x:DataType` is compiled** — misspelled or missing properties fail the build.\n2. If a subtree needs runtime binding (e.g. `BindingContext` changes dynamically), opt out with `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element.\n3. The ViewModel must be a **public** class with **public** properties, or the compiler can't resolve them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2eb470b1-dc7b-4197-9836-3395ec7abb7c","outputTokens":609,"requestId":"DC08:236247:7F387:9F9E4:69F549F1"},"id":"165ec415-671a-4497-a3e4-66a541e9e00e","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:02.344Z","parentId":"f5f9e35a-e816-4b8e-9b79-e5eaa78c6376"}
